The History of Bitcoin

What is Bitcoin?

Decentralized cryptocurrency Bitcoin (BTC) was developed in 2009 by an unidentified person or group going by the name Satoshi Nakamoto. With no ties to established financial institutions, its goal is to facilitate peer-to-peer trades without the need of middlemen like banks or governments. Miners on the blockchain network validate bitcoin transactions in exchange for fresh bitcoins. Since its launch, Bitcoin has grown to be the most well-known and significant cryptocurrency, inspiring the creation of a large number of other virtual currencies.

Investopedia

What is volume measuring?

Volume is a metric for trade activity and a good way to gauge market health. While decreasing prices with increasing volume point to a strengthening negative trend, rising markets with increasing volume are considered healthy. At fresh price highs or lows, decreasing volume might indicate a possible trend reversal.

investopedia.com

data_to_plot['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data_to_plot['Date'])

Out[]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7a444bedb820>]

The graph above is used to analyze both the highs and lows in price over a month. Often time day traders will use graphs like this to analyze trends such as supply and demand to make educated decision on when to buy and sell. In this case we could maybe conclude that holders got scared of the price fall after the peak leading to the highest volume of bitcoin being exchanged.

In[]:
plt.plot(data_to_plot['Date'].dt.day, data_to_plot['Volume'], color='green', label='High')
Out[]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7a444c37a050>]

A decline in a financial asset's price accompanied by an increase in trading volume indicates that more individuals are selling the asset. Because traders anticipate that the price will continue to decline, this suggests a greater negative trend. Thus, additional price declines are expected to follow if prices continue to decline and trading volume remains high. Comparing the two graphs, the volume appears to be spiking while the high value around that time is decreasing.

investopedia.com

What can we conclude about this data?

From this data, we can conclude that the high values are more spread out because the standard deviation is the highest among all the other standard deviation values. We can also conclude that the low values are generally more clustered together. Although, all standard deviation values are significantly high, indicating that the data is spread out.
